snippet.textDisplay: You guys called ppf which is just weird week on catalytic converters or cats for short. They don't really do much if you take them off vs leaving them on but if they get clogged and you have to fix it, it's cheaper to just remove them and not replace them. For some cars they let them run more efficient, my car gets better gas mileage now that I removed it. Some cars by taking off the cat makes them not sound so much louder but better. They may change performance stats like horsepwer by 3-5 horses  but it not enough to see a difference in a comparison.
